noun.description: A member of a mainly Hindu people primarily living in the Jammu district of the northwest Indian state of Jammu and Kashmir.

adjective.description: Relating to the Dogras or their language, Dogri.

origin: Mid 19th century; earliest use found in Alexander Burnes (1805–1841), political officer in India and explorer. From Dogri ḍogrā, self-designation.
